differences.actualValue: <speak>I see that you've arrived at the drop off location. Once the timer is over, and you’ve tried to contact the customer two times, please leave the order in a safe place, and let the customer know, by taking a photo, and leaving a note using the app. Then mark the order as delivered, and continue onto your next delivery.<break time="750ms"/></speak><speak>To listen to this message again, just say, repeat it. <break time="700ms"/> Is there anything else I can help you with today?</speak>

differences.actualValue: <speak>I'm sorry to hear that. Once you've arrived at the drop off location by following the navigation on the app, <emphasis level="strong">call</emphasis> or text the customer to start the timer. If the customer has not responded, when the timer expires, you can cancel the order, and dispose of the items. Don't worry - you'll still be paid for the delivery.<break time="750ms"/> </speak><speak>To listen to this message again, just say, repeat it. <break time="700ms"/> Is there anything else I can help you with today?</speak>
